et benefits similar to a share in a large company."), mdx("p", null, "The operation of the decentralized application is closely related to the software as such. Each Dapp uses a different infrastructure to achieve a specific goal. What they do share is the conceptual scheme. To become a decentralized application, management and administration must be carried out in a decentralized manner. For a software to be considered a dApp, it must meet the following requirements according to BlockchainHub: it must be open source, the data and log must be stored cryptographically, the application must use a cryptographic token and it must generate these automatically. In most cases, smart contracts are included for instruction execution and interconnection with the blockchain."), mdx("h2", null, "ICO DAICO ITO"));
